   &UR; NATIONAL _ GENERAL (Moved in ``a'' category) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   TOBACCO-LAWYERS (Undated) _ An arbitration panel Friday handed
out the biggest legal fees in this country's history, awarding $8.1
billion to plaintiffs' lawyers hired by three states that had sued
the tobacco companies over health care costs related to smoking. By
Barry Meier. (With graphic.)
</P>
<P>
   PUERTO-POLITICS (San Juan, P.R.) _ Sunday's vote, the subject of
heated campaigning that ended Friday with big rallies in the San
Juan metropolitan area, is a bid by the administration of Gov.
Pedro Rossello to measure the island's support for statehood and
prod Congress into authorizing a future binding vote on statehood
here.
</P>
<P>
   By Mireya Navarro.
</P>
<P>
   SCI-MARS (Kennedy Space Center, Fla.) _ The first of two NASA
science probes embarked Friday on a 416-million-mile voyage to
Mars, catapulted from Earth by a Boeing Delta 2 rocket. The
spacecraft is programmed to make the first full-scale study of
Martian weather. By Beth Dickey. (With photo.)
</P>
<P>
   GAMBLING-FEUD (Central City, Colo.) _ In this old gold-rush
landscape, modern greed over gambling is plunging two villages into
a municipal feud worthy of the Hatfields and the McCoys.By James
Brooke. (With map and photos.)
</P>
