<P>
   RETAIL-OUTLOOK (Undated) _ The recent warm weather across much
of the United States has hurt retailers, as demand has slumped for
a host of winter items ranging from tires and down-filled jackets
to snow boards and skis to sweaters and gloves. Now that
temperatures are becoming more seasonable, retail executives are
hoping the gusts of cold air will send shoppers scrambling to the
stores. By Sharon R. King.
