   IRAN-ECON (Tehran) _ Iran's economy is growing sicker by the day
as the price of Iranian oil, the export lifeblood, has dipped to a
25-year-low, forcing the government to slash imports, dig deep into
reserves, and postpone payments on foreign debts. By Douglas Jehl.
(1400 words, with graphic.)
</P>
