<P>
   MERGERS-ANTITRUST (Washington) _ With a huge plateful of large
and complex corporate mergers to review and a host of major civil
enforcement cases against corporate America's biggest names,
antitrust officials are experiencing a renaissance. Federal
officials report that they have filed a record number of challenges
this year to mergers and other anticompetitive practices and have
collected record amounts in civil fines and other penalties. By
Stephen Labaton.
