<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-12 12:22 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A6462 &Cx1f; ttc-z
u v &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-LADN-BUDGET &LR;      12-12 0211
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-LADN-BUDGET </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Sunday, Dec. 13, and thereafter. For questions about stories,
contact Stew Slavin at the Daily News, (818) 713-3702.
</P>
<P>
   McCARTHY-COLUMN _ (Los Angeles) It's been some wild ride the
kid's been on the past few months _ going from the asphalt streets
of his Los Angeles neighborhood to the dirt horseback trails of
Mammoth Lakes, then back again to get ready to ride down Colorado
Boulevard on horseback in the 1999 Tournament of Roses Parade.
Dennis McCarthy is a columnist for the Los Angeles Daily News.
(Will move in the ``k'' op-ed news file.)
</P>
<P>
   LA-FAMILIAS _ (Los Angeles) Frustrated by crime and government
neglect of their neighborhood, a group of immigrant mothers and
fathers joined to clean up their neighborhood and guide children
away from crime. They called it Familias Unidas, and they do their
good work through grants and countless hours of volunteers. On
Saturday, the mothers will make tamales to sell at the the annual
Gift of Christmas toy give-away at nearby Langdon Street
Elementary. By Yvette Cabrera. (Will move in the ``n'' California
news file.)
</P>
