for Sunday:    (The ``HNS'' tag appears in all sluglines.)   
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON NEWS (``w'' category)
</P>
<P>
   CLINTON-IMPEACHMENT (Washington) _ The House Judiciary Committee
is expected to approve a scaled-back fourth article of impeachment
against President Clinton, charging him with lying to the
committee, and then reject Democratic moves to substitute a censure
resolution. By MARK HELM.
</P>
<P>
   The Hearst News Service/Washington
</P>
</TEXT>
