receptions but has flourished under rookie coach Chan Gailey and
projects to 41 this year. That would make him only the second
``complementary'' receiver to Michael Irvin to have 40 catches the
last eight years. Here are Dallas' No. 2 wideouts since Irvin
became the primary option in '91:
</P>
