<HEADLINE>
METS IN STEP FOR HENDERSON, NOT TOTALLY OUT ON CLEMENS 
</HEADLINE>
  (lh) 
 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NASHVILLE, Tenn. _ The New York Mets kept waiting Saturday in
negotiations for Rickey Henderson and Roger Clemens.
</P>
<P>
   General Manager Steve Phillips said that he had amended his
offer to the free-agent outfielder Henderson during a 20-minute
meeting with his representatives.
</P>
<P>
   ``Not the financial terms, though,'' Phillips said of the offer,
which is believed to be for one year at about $1.7 million with
incentives and an option for a second year.
</P>
<P>
   The Mets were scheduled to meet with Henderson's representatives
again tonight.
</P>
<P>
   As for Clemens, who has demanded a trade, Phillips said he had
spoken briefly with Toronto GM Gord Ash Friday.
</P>
<P>
   ``They didn't tell us we were out,'' Phillips said.
</P>
</TEXT>
